Nalaureth
</B></font>
<BR><FONT SIZE="1" face="Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif">
Salt Miner

<BR>

<BR>
Member # 1160
<P>

</FONT>
</TD>
<TD>
<IMG SRC="http://www.tritonguild.com/tritonforum/icons/icon1.gif" BORDER="0" ALIGN="ABSCENTER">
<FONT SIZE="1" color="#a62a2a" face="Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif">
posted July 07, 2001 10:45 AM &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
<A HREF="http://www.tritonguild.com/cgi-bin/triton/ultimatebb.cgi?ubb=get_profile&u=00001160" target=_blank>
<IMG SRC="http://www.tritonguild.com/tritonforum/profile_ubb6.gif" BORDER="0" ALT="Profile for Nalaureth"></A>  &nbsp;  &nbsp;&nbsp;<A HREF="http://www.tritonguild.com/cgi-bin/triton/ultimatebb.cgi?ubb=edit_post&f=1&t=001131&reply_num=000000&u=00001160"><IMG SRC="http://www.tritonguild.com/tritonforum/edit_ubb6.gif" BORDER="0" ALT="Edit/Delete Post"></A> &nbsp;&nbsp;<A HREF="http://www.tritonguild.com/cgi-bin/triton/ultimatebb.cgi?ubb=reply&f=1&t=001131&replyto=000000"><IMG SRC="http://www.tritonguild.com/tritonforum/quote_ubb6.gif" BORDER="0" ALT="Reply With Quote"></A>
</FONT>
<HR size="1" color="#003366">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif">
After reading a fair number of posts here and elsewhere, I realize I'm taking a huge chance, that what I have to say is just as likely to result in a nasty flamefest directed at me, as in a thoughtful reconsideration of how things are done on Povar.  I half-expect, to be honest, to find myself the laughingstock of Triton and the other "ubers" of Povar. Frankly, if it happens, so be it, because I'm not going to just sit here with my thumb up my arse and be guilty of complacency.  If that ends up making me a complete pariah on Povar, fine.  At least I made the effort.<P>Several times now, I've been scheduled to go on a major raid (plane, dragon, epic mob) and arrived the usual half hour early to find some other raid group has ganked the zone or mob just ahead of us.  Last week, it was Triton in Fear.  Today, it happened again with another guild.  This time, the reason given was that some other group ganked their raid yesterday.<P>I'm tired of this kind of shit.  I'm sure everyone who's on the down side of it is also.  I'm tired of being told, well, if you wanna raid this, then join a "real" guild that "can" raid it - then being told I can't join that guild because the level limit and class limit exclude a lowly lvl XX class YY (insert your least favorite whatever there).<P>Triton is one (no offence intended here) of the most powerful guilds on Povar, and you can go anywhere and raid damn near anything.  So I'm here asking you, Giantt, and Illanae, and Wolfherz, Judadin, Tenebre, Narks, and all the other truly decent folks in this guild, to reconsider how *Triton* deals with "reserving" mobs or zones for raids, and agree to participate in a server-wide method for scheduling raids again.<P>At your levels, it's true, you can pretty much go anywhere and take whatever you want... but is that how you, each of you, wants your avatar and your guild to be known?  Hearken back to the time when you weren't lvl 60 in the best of the best gear out there... remember your first dragon raid?  Remember your first trip to Hate or Fear, the sheer *fun*... the tales of disaster ... remember those times?  Remember the feeling of accomplishment when you earned (not "were given") your first piece of planar armor?<P>Now... do any of you honestly think that it's at all fun for 30-40 people to show up for a raid, usually with some epic riding on the line, to find that guild XYZ got half an hour's jump on them and went in/up ahead of them?  And does anyone think that offering those of us who didn't get to go a shot to come up and loot armor they didn't fight for really will satisfy us?  (Yes, I know, for some folks, it's about the loot, and who gives a damn how they get it as long as they have the best and the first.  Well.  How many bests and firsts are still left for you?  And how would taking CT out *again* be a best or first in that scheme?)<P>I'm appealing to Triton because if you all agree to follow some sort of scheduling system, the rest of the guilds on server are more likely to respect that system as well.  I'm not asking you to overthrow agreements such as the rotation you have with RA - just participate in *one* schedule posted in *one* place with a few rules like not being able to post more than a few weeks in advance, and everyone respecting everyone else's raids when posted.  Pickup raids would be exempt.<P>I'm asking that we set up some means for other guilds or guild alliances to move up to the next level, the next mob or zone.  Should any guild have to prove themselves to another before they should be able to take a shot at some mob or zone?  What's the worst that can happen?  - if they fail, then guess what, they failed, and there's still plenty of room for a cleanup raid by Triton or RA or whoever *can* do it.  No obligation by anyone to even help with CR ... just letting people have a shot at something.<P>The reason Krohn gave me last week, regarding Fear, was that Triton was only going after CT and the miniboss draco (since it was their turn per the rotation with RA) ... but Triton didn't have the time to wait for the Alliance to clear Fear ahead of them, and the Alliance raiders would just have been a liability to the Triton operation.<P>Ever wonder why some people have such a negative opinion of Triton?  Well... consider the message the Alliance people got out of that:  "We're going up because we're more powerful than you and we've decided we want to, so bugger off."  What do you expect people to think of Triton after something like that?  And on a personal level: do you *want* people thinking of your guild that way?  Of you?  Do you care?<P>(If you don't care, btw, if you're content to be part of a system that cheats everyone else of the fun they might have, or you don't give a flying fuck at a rolling donut about us "n00b whiners", just ignore everything I've said, hop to that reply screen, and hit me with the flames now.)<P>Here's another scenario, one that could have played out but didn't because the Alliance people remained reasonable about things:   Had we invoked the Play Nice Policy, we had every right to go up to Fear right alongside Triton's raid group.  Had Triton's raid refused to share the spawns up there, someone could have called in a GM, and the solution that would have been mandated, were Triton and the Alliance raiders unwilling to agree to share the zone, would have been that each group would get exactly half of the mobs, alternating pulls.  That's as written in the rules, which, regardless of whether Triton chooses to agree with or subscribe to, still apply.<P>(And yes, it would have been hell on lag and probably resulted in a lot of deaths, mostly for us lower level characters.  But people do a lot of stupid things on principle, and maybe in the end, those things aren't so stupid).<P>I personally don't want to see things come to that pass; I don't think anyone does.  I would suggest that if there is a guild out there that refuses to participate, then those who *do* abide by the schedule, and respect each others' raids, simply pull the PnP on that guild.  If it happens enough times, they will get the message - and we'll all still be working within the rules.<P>So.  What will it be?  Is Triton, as a guild, and are you, as individuals, willing to work with the other guilds and players on Povar to come up with a more equitable system than the current one which rewards only those who need the least amount of sleep and don't have jobs to worry about?<P>Heh think about it... do you really want the pilot of your next transatlantic flight, or the driver of the semi right behind you on the off-ramp, to be someone who stayed up all night just so they could finally get in on that Fear or Hate raid that had to be at 3am their time in order that all the other guilds didn't get there first?<P>--Nalaureth sul'Fate<BR>GL, Hands of Faith (Povar)<BR>51 Ranger of Kelethin
</FONT>
<HR size="1" color="#003366">
