hey there, Nala!  missj00lubj00lots!<P>as for your post... i wish you the best of luck on getting something like what you suggest started.  unfortunately, it seems like "uber" guilds tend to fall into that pattern that all social groups exhibit eventually: many of them are, when on their own, excellent folks.  however, get them all together and "threaten" them with a suggestion for any sort of change that would ultimately end up costing them a bit of patience, and watch the reasonable ones disappear...<P>i have the utmost respect for the people i know and am fond of in triton; that's the way it works for everyone, in my book. it don't matter what guild, or if they play EQ, or if they enjoy romantic escapades with the occasional frozen chicken.  decent folks are decent folks, and i hope that you gain enough support from them to prevail over the l3wtwhores.<P>also, let me know if you ever need some help with a raid.  i don't play much at all, but if you post over on the <A HREF="http://www.guardianbrotherhood.com" TARGET=_blank>Guardian Brotherhood</A> <A HREF="http://pub4.ezboard.com/bguardianbrotherhood" TARGET=_blank>message board</A>, we'll get you some folks, and i may even dust the cobwebs off the keyboard...<P>so - to nala, good luck!  and to triton - karma is a beautiful thing!<P>  <IMG SRC="biggrin.gif" border="0"><P>--------------------<P><I><B>Kitsu Mindspire</B>, Sorcerer for Hire</I><BR>Freelance Harlot<BR>Patron Goddess of Delicious Wickedness<BR><I>Inspiring the masses to indulgence since 2000e.v.</I><BR>^_^
