<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif">
Hello Nalaureth,<P>Let me first start by saying I respect your opinions and ideas.  You did a nice job of putting that post together.  Secondly, let me appologize for any actions last week that may have hurt your raiding plans.<P>Now, you must understand.  Triton does stuff that almost *never* interferes with other guilds these days so in our eyes, there is no reason to goto this system.  The one thing that we do that may interfere with another guilds raiding plans is Cazic Thule, ever other pop, as does RA.  That's 1 day out of 7 though.   <IMG SRC="smile.gif" border="0"><P>I'm guessing you're a fairly new player on Povar (no offense intended, seriously   <IMG SRC="smile.gif" border="0">) so you probably don't know that there was, at one time, a reservation system in tact.  Every single time an 'uber guild' tried to use this system they would get flamed to no end for it.  What it came down to is that the system never worked.  There were always people who refused to follow it and you can't force someone to.  Same thing will happen here.<P>I highly doubt you will get the Officers and Leader of Triton to agree to a reservation system souly for the fact that we do almost *nothing* that can interfere with another guilds plans.  Let me give you some examples:<P><B>Plane of Fear</B> - We do this once every other CT pop, that's it.<P><B>Plane of Hate</B> - Last time we had a guild effort to devistate PoH was after the plane was revamped.  We haven't been back since.<P><B>Plane of Sky</B> - We do 12 man raids here and not very often.  PoS isn't used much anyways, so not a problem here.<P><B>Plane of Growth</B> - Last time we were here was, what, 4 months ago?   <IMG SRC="smile.gif" border="0"><P><B>Epic Mobs</B> - Most of our members have their epics completed.  Those who don't either wait for a camp to be free before camping it (see:Ragefire) or have battles to do.<P><B>Venril Sathir</B> - Been forver since the last time we've killed him.<P><B>Trakanon</B> - Can't even remember the last time we killed him.<P>See what I mean?  There's really no reason for us to participate in the reservation system.  Perhaps you may want to bring this up to guilds who still do these sort of things on a daily or weekly basis.<P>Now, going to nit pick some of your original post.<P>  <BLOCKQUOTE><font size="1" face="Verdana, Arial">quote:</font><HR>Several times now, I've been scheduled to go on a major raid (plane, dragon, epic mob) and arrived the usual half hour early to find some other raid group has ganked the zone or mob just ahead of us. Last week, it was Triton in Fear. Today, it happened again with another guild. This time, the reason given was that some other group ganked their raid yesterday.<HR></BLOCKQUOTE><P>Ok, but from what I heard your Alliance raid which we 'crashed' was being tossed together about an hour before we started heading to the portal.  Now, we had been planing on Fear that entire day and as early as 3 days before that.  I think the Alliance had like 15 people or so in Feerrott and I didn't see any of you at the portal.<P>  <BLOCKQUOTE><font size="1" face="Verdana, Arial">quote:</font><HR>Now... do any of you honestly think that it's at all fun for 30-40 people to show up for a raid, usually with some epic riding on the line, to find that guild XYZ got half an hour's jump on them and went in/up ahead of them?<HR></BLOCKQUOTE><P>I think you'll find that Triton is one of the more courteous 'uber guilds' when it comes to this.  Our officers are very reasonable and don't want to ruin peoples plans.  If we had found a raiding party of 30-40 at the Fear portal when we got there we certainly would have backed off... however, that was not the case.  15-20 people MAX in Feerrott for the Alliance raid, none at the portal.<P>  <BLOCKQUOTE><font size="1" face="Verdana, Arial">quote:</font><HR>Ever wonder why some people have such a negative opinion of Triton? Well... consider the message the Alliance people got out of that: "We're going up because we're more powerful than you and we've decided we want to, so bugger off."<HR></BLOCKQUOTE><P>Then you got the wrong message.  The message was: "We're prepared first.  We have a solid break team where as you and the other guild here at the portal do not.  We're going in."  You also may want to look back at that day (I can post a few quotes from my logs   <IMG SRC="wink.gif" border="0">) and see what the Alliance people were shouting and oocing.  They were saying some very nasty things to Triton.  Two wrongs don't make a right.  Also, take this in consideration.  There were three guilds in Feerrott, two of them (Triton and The Stoic) were ready to go in (Stoic was waiting for another Cleric I believe).  If we would have backed down you still would have had to contend with them.<P>  <BLOCKQUOTE><font size="1" face="Verdana, Arial">quote:</font><HR>Here's another scenario, one that could have played out but didn't because the Alliance people remained reasonable about things: Had we invoked the Play Nice Policy, we had every right to go up to Fear right alongside Triton's raid group.<HR></BLOCKQUOTE> <P>Actually, this has been attempted to be done before.  End result, in every case mind you, has been that the guild who is prepared enough to go into Fear gets it.  The Alliance that was in Feerrott that day was far from prepared to go in.<P>  <BLOCKQUOTE><font size="1" face="Verdana, Arial">quote:</font><HR>I would suggest that if there is a guild out there that refuses to participate, then those who *do* abide by the schedule, and respect each others' raids, simply pull the PnP on that guild.<HR></BLOCKQUOTE><P>PnP'ing a guild because they don't follow a system you're trying to put together is worse than racing a guild to a spawn.  Have you ever been PnP'd before?  It sucks.  It really sucks.  Also, if you can PnP them when they want to goto a place you've reserved, what is going to stop THEM from PnP'ing YOU when YOUR at a spawn YOU reserved.  I think if anything they'd do it more because you're doing it to them.  This is why the system can't and won't work.<P>  <BLOCKQUOTE><font size="1" face="Verdana, Arial">quote:</font><HR>So. What will it be? Is Triton, as a guild, and are you, as individuals, willing to work with the other guilds and players on Povar to come up with a more equitable system than the current one which rewards only those who need the least amount of sleep and don't have jobs to worry about?<HR></BLOCKQUOTE><P>To be completly honest ('growing up' in a time when there was a reservation system and a time when there isn't one) I have to say that I much perfer Povar the way it is now.  When we had a reservation system it was HELL.  PURE HELL.  I'm guessing you're a fairly new player (no offense intended) who didn't experience both those times.  You're lucky.  The reservation system sucked.<P>  <BLOCKQUOTE><font size="1" face="Verdana, Arial">quote:</font><HR>to be someone who stayed up all night just so they could finally get in on that Fear or Hate raid that had to be at 3am their time in order that all the other guilds didn't get there first?<HR></BLOCKQUOTE><P>Just a little comment on this one.  The Fear portal was *empty* until like 5pm EST.  If you wanted to go, you should have tried to get there earlier.<P>Anyway, these are my ideas and opinions.  I'm not an officer of Triton, simply a member.  If you want to discuss this further feel free to shoot me a tell in game.   <IMG SRC="wink.gif" border="0"><P>--------------------<P> <IMG SRC="http://www.tritonguild.com/images/rombsig.gif"> <BR><A HREF="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=5696" TARGET=_blank>Rombus [60 Sorcerer]</A><BR><A HREF="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=5702" TARGET=_blank>Rommy [60 High Priest]</A>
