<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif">
Nalaureth, what are you hoping to accomplish?<P>If you are hoping to establish the support of Triton in creating a reservation system, let me just say that it will not happen, I'm sorry.  Triton and the other guilds on the server, especially the higher level ones, have seen what the reservation system did... I think I speak for us all when I say we NEVER want to see one in place again.<P>What I would suggest doing is dealing with each situation as it comes up.  Talk with the officers of whatever guild you're having problems with and work something out.  <P>The reason why we didn't work with you that day was because unlike other planned days we didn't have that option.  We already had plans later in the evening and simply didn't have time to wait for you to clear.  We needed it ASAP so we could kill and move on.  Draco was also up, he would have caused significant issues for you while pulling and you most likely would not have been able to defeat him.<P> <BLOCKQUOTE><font size="1" face="Verdana, Arial">quote:</font><HR>Make Triton's name one that everyone points to when they speak of the exceptions to "uberness." The way I envision you doing that is, when you find out there's a raid planned for someplace you're going, at around the same time as your own raid, you make some effort to work out a compromise.<HR></BLOCKQUOTE><P>As stated previously, WE DO THIS.  We do this in every instance we encounter a problem.  LIKE I STATED BEFORE, we DON&#8217;T usually do things that compete with guilds OTHER than R.A.  When our plans end up conflicting with another guilds plans, we work out a compromise.  We&#8217;ve always done this and we shall continue to do this.<P> <BLOCKQUOTE><font size="1" face="Verdana, Arial">quote:</font><HR>What happened the Friday before last wasn't a compromise, it was a steamroller - it was "We're going up because we don't think you're ready to go up, and it's our turn anyway, so bugger off." There was no discussion - just someone in Triton making a conscious decision to ignore Eronmore and the Alliance raid, rather than advise your own raid leader of the situation and let the raid leaders work something out.<HR></BLOCKQUOTE><P>If you wish to see it that way, you&#8217;re certainly allowed to.  REALIZE &#8211; we were racing one other guild as it was, The Stoic.  I personally was not aware of the Alliance Raid until we had already zoned in and there were about 15 of you in the zone shouting things at us.  It certainly was not &#8220;We're going up because we don't think you're ready to go up, and it's our turn anyway, so bugger off.&#8221;  It was more like, &#8220;You guys aren&#8217;t prepared &#8211; we know this for a fact, you don&#8217;t have the force in the zone at the moment.  The Stoic is also racing us.  If we wait for you guys to gather, lose.&#8221;  Please, stop putting words in our mouth because you clearly are not aware of the entire situation.<P>I&#8217;m personally sorry for messing up your plans and allow me to inform you of how you can avoid this in the future.<P>Mistake 1.) You told a_random_Triton_member03 in Feerrott of your intent <B>hoping</B> he would relay that to an officer.  That&#8217;s the wrong way of doing things, as a guild leader you should understand this.  <IMG SRC="wink.gif" border="0"><P>How to Resolve This - /tell a_random_Triton_member03 Can I please have a name of an officer online?  I wish to speak to them.  That member would then give you the name of an officer online and you can work out a compromise.<P>Mistake 2.) You assumed Triton was racing you to Fear.<P>Actual Situation &#8211; We had been planning this raid all morning and were waiting for sufficient force to start the break.  When we had the force we found out that The Stoic was on route to Feerrott too.  We mobilized and started the race.  We were not even aware of the Alliance raid until later when someone decided to contact a Triton officer to work something out&#8230; however you were to late.  You waited until we were buffing to break to try to work out a compromise.  <P>Mistake 3.) Instead of trying to further work out the situation your people started shouting and taunting Triton members in the zone for (and I quote from my logs) &#8220;ruining our raid just like you ruin everyone else&#8217;s.&#8221;<P>What you Should Have Done &#8211; Contacted an officer and discussed your needs.  The Stoic acknowledged that we had won the race and worked out a compromise.  They needed two items from Fear, an item for the SK epic and if it was up, the mob for the Enchanter epic.  We told them that if either of these items/spawns were up, they could loot them.  You could have talked to Krohn and said that you simply wanted the items from normal mobs.  If you would have said this, you probably would have gotten better results.  It&#8217;s not our job to create a compromise for you, it&#8217;s your job to compromise and propose things to us. L<P>I seriously hope I&#8217;m not being to harsh, that&#8217;s not my intent.  I simply want you to know that there was more to the situation than meets the eye and things you could have done (and can do in the future) to prevent this sort of thing from happening again.  Several of your members contacted me and asked if any items dropped for their class if they could be contacted to loot&#8230; I kept track and called them in if something was rotting, no reason we couldn&#8217;t have done this on a more massive scale for the entire raiding party. <P>Let me just recap for ya. J<BR>--Reservation System and Support of Triton for this, No.<BR>--Contact an officer directly when you have problems, don&#8217;t go through members.<BR>--Make suggestions for a compromise.  Usually an officer who is trying to organize a raid is to caught up in the actual raid to think up suggestions, it&#8217;s a hell of a job.<BR>--Get the whole story before making assumptions.<BR>--We don&#8217;t steamroll.<P>Good luck, and again, don&#8217;t take this harshly please.<P>--------------------<P> <IMG SRC="http://www.tritonguild.com/images/rombsig.gif"> <BR><A HREF="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=5696" TARGET=_blank>Rombus [60 Sorcerer]</A><BR><A HREF="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=5702" TARGET=_blank>Rommy [60 High Priest]</A>
