<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif">
Let me just recap for ya. J<BR>--Reservation System and Support of Triton for this, No.<P>** You already have one.  Very limited, yes, but your agreement with RA is a variation on that theme.  The only reason a calendar system won't work on Povar is because people don't want to make the effort to follow it.  The pissing matches between ubers are too much fun, I suspect, and people get off on beating out the other guilds even on petty shit.  But ok, you've answered my question.**<P>--Contact an officer directly when you have problems, dont go through members.<P>** I attempted just exactly this.  I don't recall whom I asked for that information, but I was told to speak to Krohn, who, based on what he said and based on what the Triton member who pointed me to him said, sounded as though he was both an officer and the raid leader.  At no time in the conversation did Krohn say or act otherwise.  So... don't see where exactly I handled that wrong.  I did what I could with the information I had from your own members.  I can't help that they steered me wrong.**<P>--Make suggestions for a compromise. Usually an officer who is trying to organize a raid is to caught up in the actual raid to think up suggestions, its a hell of a job.<P>** I *made* suggestions.  None of them were to Krohn's liking, because they all revolved around somehow cooperating with the Alliance groups raiding jointly with Triton in Fear, and the Triton raid didn't want to have to wait or deal with anyone else in the zone.<P>Now, maybe I'm missing some things here... Triton was racing Stoic... but you only have the agreement with RA... because only Triton and RA, I am informed, are able to take on CT and Draco.  What I'm having trouble with is two things:  you cooperate with other guilds, and you won't support a calendar system, yet you have one with RA for this zone, and you exclude the Stoic (and presumably anyone else) from that arrangement, forcing them into racing Triton or RA to Fear when CT is up.  And you won't cooperate with the Alliance when it happens to have a planned raid starting only a short while later.  This sounds very much like a selective reservation system to me, one that serves Triton's and RA's purposes while leaving any other guilds out in the cold.  Please tell me where I'm misunderstanding how things work.<P>My point being, why bother racing Stoic if they cannot take out CT?  If they cannot, there's a wipeout at the end of their raid, and CT and Draco are left up for Triton to go in and take.  And if they can, why are they not part of the rotation agreement with RA?<P>--Get the whole story before making assumptions.<P>** Hmmm.  I spoke at length with Krohn.  If he failed to inform me of the whole story, I'm not sure what else I'm supposed to do other than perhaps start learning to read minds.  I don't see what assumptions I've made, except that a Triton guild member on the raid would inform me correctly of any officers online.  Obviously, I thought wrong.<P>You mention logs of what Alliance people were saying in Feerrott zone... if that's the case, how can you claim to have been ignorant of the Alliance guild raid?  (And, btw, yes, they were hotheaded ... big surprise, surely you didnt' expect them to just shrug and say, oh, ok, we'll respect this agreement Triton has with RA even though they won't respect our scheduled raid that is already forming up, right now.  I don't think they handled it well, and had I personally be in the zone, rather than stopping en route in Innothule when I heard Triton was going up, I would have done my best to get things out of the vernacular and into the problem-solving.  But that milk is spilt already.)<P>I don't, btw, expect you to have held off going up at the risk of losing the zone to Stoic, it is first come first served.  I didn't actually ask for that.  I asked that we be allowed to bring our raid parties up into Fear and deal with the spawns that would be little exp for your group, spawns that would have been great exp and great fun for our group.  It simply wasn't deemed convenient by the Triton people raiding - didn't fit with their plans for their raid, to attempt to cooperate with those who tried very hard, you must admit, to work around the known fact of the Triton/RA alternating agreement.<P>You ask what I want.  Well.  How about this?  Krohn could have spoken with Eronmore, found out when our party was expecting to embark, explained the situation with the Stoic, and offered to go up to hold the zone for both your party and ours.  Could have invited our groups to come up and work on clearing, even if that meant a little slower going getting to CT.  Admit it, once Triton was in Fear, it's not like the race with Stoic continued.  It's not like they were up there with you trying to get to CT and Draco first.<P>As Krohn put it to me, Triton works best doing  Fear with a smallish team of about 20, and prefers to go through it fast.  He also made it abundantly clear to me that the Triton raid found it inconvenient to allow our raid parties to participate, because your raid wanted to blow through the zone as fast as possible.  Fine, that's honest, and I respect the honesty.  But be honest with me now and admit that Krohn told it like it is: Triton *didn't want to bother* with any kind of cooperation with the Alliance raiders.  It wasn't *convenient* for Triton to slow its raid down a little bit to accommodate people who had worked their asses off to accommodate Triton/RA plans.<P>--We dont steamroll.<BR>So you were racing Stoic to get to CT/Draco, and that's why you went up with your pickup raid in the face of a long-planned Alliance raid due to head up half an hour later - that you had to get to CT first.  That's not steamrolling?<P>Let me ask this:  in all honesty, had Triton arrived at the portal and found out that there was an Alliance raid in the making, and Stoic was *not* pushing to beat you to zone-in, would that really have changed how things played out?  If no one was racing you to CT, would you have been willing to go up jointly and let the Alliance parties handle the lesser mobs?  Or would you still have been driving to get to CT/Draco as fast as possible, and not wanted to bother with that?<P>The Alliance raid posed absolutely no threat to your target, nor was that our goal, yet we were turned down for anything other than the rather demeaning "come up and loot our scraps" offer - which loot, as I've said before, was not the primary reason for our raid.  We had someone with an epic we were hoping to help him finish, and we hoped to have some fun together.<P>All I've heard so far is, and I don't mean to sound harsh, but the facts *are* harsh - justifications and rationalizations for Triton doing what you damn well pleased.<P>To summarize:<BR>- The Alliance raid was somehow expected to just know that Triton/RA would be after the respawned CT and therefore stand aside while the big boys jockeyed for position.  We were supposed to reschedule our long-planned raid to accommodate your short term changes in plans.<BR>- It's somehow my fault that a compromise wasn't reached because a Triton member pointed me to the wrong person to discuss the problem with at the time, and then the person I was discussing it with wasn't willing to consider any compromises that would have allowed us to raid.  Apparently, in your eyes, suggesting any compromises you won't accept is the same thing as me not suggesting them.  Ok. I see how that is.<P>I see I'm expecting the impossible.  I'm asking for common decency and simple courtesy, respect, and an attempt to work out things in a way differently than it was handled.  I don't see anyone here making any other suggestions besides some sort of central calendar for the server so we all know who's going where when so we don't step on each others' toes as happened this last time.<P>I did all I could to work things out at the time, and it seems like the only response I'm getting is nitpicking all the ways in which I'm responsible for the actions/inaction of others.  Ok, I get it.  I'd hoped that Triton the guild was more like the generous and considerate Triton members I knew, and now I see Kit was right that getting a group of powerplayers together results in the loss of their ability to act as a decent part of a larger community.<P>All I can say is, how can you wonder about your guild's reputation on the server?  How can it come as a surprise to you?<P>Rombus, I hope you understand that I do respect your keeping the communication unantagonistic, and I hope you realize I've tried to do the same.  I'm angry, yes, and disappointed that a group of people who have the power to change things don't have the will to do so, but it's no particular surprise to me that those who benefit most from the status quo have no desire to change it.  I'm an idealist, and in one thing, I'm glad I was not disappointed:  I expected, truly, to be reamed and flamed within an inch of my life, and that didnt' happen.  We may disagree, but I respect that you were willing to discuss the matter with me and keep it civilized.  I'll drop it now because there's nothing else left to say.<P>Nalaureth sul'Fate<BR>GL, Hands of Faith (Povar)<BR>51 Ranger of Kelethin
