<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif">
Well, I was one of the original members of NA(now FU), and was one of the people that originally fought for the reservation system.  Boy, what a mistake that was.<P>All the reservation system did was cause problems.  People would reserve such small things as FGs for 3 months in advance.  It just doesn't work when most of the larger guilds on Povar operate on a "spur-of-the-moment"-type schedule.  Half the time, we end up doing more than planned, as we finished our original plan early, or vice versa.  I am sure this happens with the other guilds.<P>The reservation would severly restrict this freedom, and thus would disallow many guilds the ability to do raids on impulse.<P>So to further enforce would Rombus said, just because one zone is taken, there are many, many out there that are still available.  Plane of Hate, Sky, Growth, Sebilis Juggernauts/reets/named, are just the tip of the iceburg.  <P>I know you are just trying to stick up for your guild and the Alliance's best interests, but please understand that the reservation system was tested several times throughout the history of Povar, and has failed miserably every time.  Check the backlogs of the Povar EQvault messageboard to see the reasons in-depth.<P>Good luck in your raiding endeavors, however. <P>-Gruffy
</FONT>
